						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							River otters are aquatic mammals, meaning they love the water. They live along the banks of rivers, ponds, and dams. Otters prefer water bordered by woods. River otters are expert swimmers and love to play and swim by flexing their long bodies up and down, paddling with their webbed back feet, and using their feet and strong tails to steer.
						</text>
