						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							Otters are skilled hunters too and can hold their breath for up to 4 minutes underwater! They eat fish the most, but will also eat crustaceans, small mammals, rodents, and even fruit! Otters catch fish in their mouths and hold the fish on their stomach to eat while they float on their back in the water. If the fish is too big they will bring it on land to dine.
						</text>
